# Distributed Game of Life — Agent Context

## Project Overview
A distributed, real-time Game of Life played in a browser viewport. Players can
place individual cells or pre-defined shapes on a shared infinite grid. The
simulation runs server-side; clients receive chunk updates via WebSocket and
apply local predictive ticks for responsiveness.

## Repository Layout
```
/                   Go module root
├── main.go         HTTP server entry-point (WebSocket upgrade, static serving)
├── gateway/        HTTP handlers, shape catalog, rate-limiting middleware
├── simulation/     Conway tick engine, chunk management
├── ratelimit/      Token-bucket rate limiter (per-player)
├── storage/        Redis persistence layer
├── metrics/        Prometheus metrics
└── viewport/       Browser frontend (vanilla JS + CSS)
    ├── index.html
    ├── app.js      Main client logic (camera, WebSocket, render loop)
    └── style.css
```

## Architecture Notes
- **Server tick rate**: ~250 ms (matches `LOCAL_TICK_MS` in `app.js`).
- **Chunk size**: 64x64 cells. Clients subscribe to the chunks in their viewport.
- **Rate limiting**: Token bucket — 50 max tokens, 5 tokens/sec refill, 1 token
  per cell spawned. Tracked client-side for instant UI feedback and enforced
  server-side for correctness.
- **WebSocket message types**:
  - Client → Server: `SUBSCRIBE`, `UNSUBSCRIBE`, `SPAWN`, `PLACE_SHAPE`
  - Server → Client: `CHUNK_STATE`, `SPAWN_ACK`, `PLACE_SHAPE_ACK`, `ERROR`

## Frontend Conventions
- `localCells` is a `Map<"x,y", hslColorString>` — **not** a plain Set.
  Every cell carries its own pastel HSL color.
- Cells born via Game-of-Life rules inherit a circular average of their
  neighbors' colors; user-placed cells get a fresh random pastel.
- No external JS frameworks or bundlers — plain ES2020 in a single `app.js`.

## Key Config Constants (app.js)
| Constant | Value | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `BASE_CELL_SIZE` | 8 px | Pixel size of one cell at zoom 1× |
| `CHUNK_SIZE` | 64 | Cells per chunk edge |
| `LOCAL_TICK_MS` | 250 ms | Local prediction interval |
| `VIEWPORT_PAD` | 1 | Extra chunks subscribed beyond visible edge |
| `RL_MAX` / `RL_REFILL` | 50 / 5 | Rate-limit token bucket |

## Deployment
- Cloud Run (single container). See `deploy.ps1` and `DEPLOYMENT.md`.
- Redis (Memorystore) for cell persistence.
- Secrets managed via Cloud Secret Manager.
